        <td valign="top" height="2151px">
           <div style="position:relative;">
<div style="width:675px; height:2151px; display:inline-block; position:absolute; left:0px; top:0px">
<div style="text-align: center;"><i>Updated: 7/2/2014</i></div><br><div><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">EIS Tax Relief<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><b><font color="#000000" face="Georgia, serif"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt;">Q: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Are investors&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 15px;">definitely</span><span style="font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;able to claim EIS tax relief &nbsp;on their share purchases?<o:p></o:p></span></font></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 11.5pt;">A: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span><font face="arial" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium;">&nbsp;</font><font size="3" face="times new roman"><font color="#000000">We have a very high level of confidence that all (tax-paying) investors will be able to claim 30% tax relief on their share purchase(s). However, every scheme has to be approved by HMRC in advance and we're still waiting to hear from&nbsp;the Tax Office. We filed our application in December 2013, so we're hoping to be able to provide a definitive answer by the end of this month (February 2014). &nbsp;</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Pledges<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Q: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Is it too late to Pledge?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="text-indent: -36pt;"><font face="Georgia, serif"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt;"><font color="#000000">A: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font color="#000099"><b>Absolutely not!</b></font><font color="#000000"> We set the January 31st deadline for pledges so that we could start negotiations with STAG as quickly as possible.</font></span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;In reality, the opportunity to submit pledges will be open until we either reach our target (£350,000) or agree a purchase price with STAG. We hope to reach our target in&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 15px;">the</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;next few weeks, so&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 15px;">our</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;advice is not to wait too long, or you could miss out.</span></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="text-indent: -36pt;"><font color="#000000" face="Georgia, serif"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt;"><br></span></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"><br></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Q: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Will my pledge be confidential?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">A: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Yes, your name and the amount you have pledged will initially only be known to the Treasurer.&nbsp; When a company has been formed, funds requested and shares issued, the shareholder details will be available from Companies House in the normal way.&nbsp; Because of this confidentiality, you may still be approached by members of the working party or the community encouraging you to make a pledge; please do not be offended if this happens – it is because nobody knows whether you have pledged already or not!<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Q: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Will the total amount pledged to date be publicised?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">A: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Initially yes; from time-to-time, the Treasurer will be making available to the working party Chairman a summary of the number of people giving pledges, the total funds raised, and some analysis of the levels of pledging.&nbsp; This information may be announced during the initial fund-raising period.&nbsp; However, as we approach our target, the working-party intends to keep the total sum that has been pledged strictly confidential, to ensure that the purchase negotiations are not compromised buy public knowledge of what our total funding is.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Buying the Pub<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Q:&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; What if Stag get a commercial offer for the pub before we have raised our community funds?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">A:&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Firstly, many people in the community would welcome the pub being bought by a suitably qualified and motivated buyer who wanted to make the pub a success, and would regard such an offer as a positive thing.&nbsp; But even if an offer was being talked about, we need to press on with our fundraising.&nbsp;&nbsp; This is because many offers fail to complete, so we should not be distracted by the possibility of another buyer. Also, should a commercial buyer not make a success of the pub after a year or two, we will want to ‘dust off’ our pledges and proposals and save our pub once again.&nbsp; Finally, the community should be notified of any impending purchase under the terms of the community asset listing, so we get a chance to see where we stand (see further notes on this elsewhere in the Q&amp;A).<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"><br></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><b><font color="#000000" face="Georgia, serif"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt;">Q: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Stag is a family business and two of it's directors live in the village. If we negotiate to buy the pub as a community then do we risk </span><span style="font-size: 15px;">alienating</span><span style="font-size: 11.5pt;">&nbsp;or excluding them in some way?&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 11.5pt;">A: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman, serif" size="3">There is no hostility implicit in our campaign to fund a community pub. Stag wish to sell the pub and we would like to buy it (which is a good start for business), but our main goal is to secure the long-term future of the pub. In this respect we would welcome and support any other buyers who are equally committed to making the pub work.&nbsp;</font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman, serif" size="3">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; We are very mindful of the fact that Jess and her family live in&nbsp;the village and will endeavour to ensure that they feel included in this venture (as members of&nbsp;the community). Although we have some difficult negotiations ahead of us, there is no reason why we can't do business together in a friendly and professional manner.</font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"><br></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span><b style="font-size: 11pt; text-indent: -1cm;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Q: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Can the proposed Nupend Farm development somehow contribute to funding the pub?</span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 11.5pt; text-indent: -1cm;">&nbsp; A: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Not really.&nbsp; Although the developers have suggested that they would be willing to make a financial contribution to the community (either directly, or via what is called a ‘Schedule 106 Planning Gain), this is not going to help the pub project for three important reasons.&nbsp; Firstly, we want to avoid any divisiveness in the village, and we certainly don’t want to create any possibility of a conflict between people who are ‘pro-pub’ and those who are ‘anti-development’, so it is important to keep these two important issues separate.&nbsp; Secondly, even if we all wanted to do it, there really is no practical mechanism to reliably link any concessions to the developers with a deal on the pub, as any Planning Gain funding would be controlled by Stroud.&nbsp; Finally, the timing is unlikely to work; we need to buy the pub in the next few months, whereas the Nupend development is likely to spend a year or more in protracted planning arguments.</span></p><div class="AppleOriginalContents" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; direction: ltr;"><div style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 1cm; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -1cm;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"><br></span></div></div><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Running the Pub<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Q: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; What should I do if I am interested in being a supplier to the pub, the manager, working there, or otherwise being involved in the business?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">A: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Please let us know of your interest by email to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:thepub@horsleyparish.co.uk" style="color: rgb(149, 79, 114);">thepub@horsleyparish.co.uk</a>&nbsp;and we will try to get back to you.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Planning<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Q: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Is there a planning condition about the pub being finished before the houses can be sold?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">A:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Yes, there is a planning condition that the pub must be ‘available for use’ before the third house can be ‘occupied’.&nbsp; Stag have now applied for this condition to be lifted as they say that the pub is ‘available for us’.&nbsp; There is no clarity around what ‘available for use’ really means and we have been discussing this with Stroud District Council</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><b style="font-size: 11pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><b style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Q: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b><font color="#000000" face="Georgia, serif"><span style="font-size: 15px;"><b>What is the community asset listing and what is the effect of the listing?</b></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 11.5pt;">A: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span style="text-indent: -36pt; font-size: 15px;"><font color="#000000" face="Georgia, serif">Thanks to a nomination by the Parish Council, the whole Bell &amp; Castle site is listed by SDC as an ‘asset of community value’ under the Localism Act. This means that the developers cannot sell the pub until they have notified SDC of the intended sale, and we the community have been given six weeks to decide whether we want to put in a rival bid for the property (the initial moratorium). The legislation contains an exception which says that if at the time of the sale the pub business is being ‘carried on’ and the business is a ‘going concern’ then the developers don’t have to notify the council, but the meaning of the exception is uncertain. In any event there is a restriction on the title at the Land Registry which says that the requirements of the Localism Act must be met before a sale can take place.</font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><font color="#000000" face="Georgia, serif"><span style="font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;</span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; text-indent: -36pt;"><font color="#000000" face="Georgia, serif"><span style="font-size: 15px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; If during the initial moratorium the community decides to put in a bid for the property, it has the option of doing so in a way that triggers a full six month moratorium during which time the developers cannot sell to a third party, thereby giving the community in effect a six month negotiation period. The Act does not however require the developers to sell the property to the community even if we make a suitable offer.</span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"><br></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Background to the Site<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><b><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Q: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I heard that Alex Kerr has disputed something in the Prospectus, is that right?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">A: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Yes. In the prospectus we said that at one point Mr Kerr submitted a plan ‘seeking the demolition of the pub and replacing it with six houses’; he has now clarified this by saying all plans he submitted included a pub of some sort on the site.&nbsp; Also, we suggested that Mr Kerr having sold the site had ‘given up on the project’; but he tells us he is still very much interested in the development of the site, and indeed he attended the meeting on 12 January and said he was very supportive of our plans.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 72pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-indent: -36pt;"><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"><br></span></p></div>
</div>
           </div>
        </td>
